What is S3?
============
1) Stands for  simple storeage service
2) So S3 provides developers  and IT teams with secure, durable, highly scalable object storage.
3) Amazon S3 is easy to use with simple web service interface to store and retrieve any amount of data from anywhere on
    the web.
4) S3 is a safe place to store the files. that measn it is used to strre the data as an object or flat files, picture, 
    word document, movies 
5) It is object based storage 
6) The data is spreadh accross multiple site and facilities.

baiscs of S3
============
1) S3 is object based. i.e. it allows you to upload files.
2) Files can be from 0 B to 5 TB
3) There is unlimited storage
4) Files are stored in buckets.
Note that bucket here is just a folder inside S3
5) S3 is a universal namespace. That means, the names given to S3 must be unique globally.
6) When you upload a file to S3 you are goinf to receive a HTTP 200  to your browser if the upload was successful.
